ans : 


On which services are configured with the AWS SNS ?
ans : Amazon Simple Notification Service (AWS SNS) is configured with various AWS services, such as Amazon S3, Lambda, EC2, and others, to enable event-driven 
      communication and notifications within the AWS cloud ecosystem.

What is 10DLC in AWS ?
ans : Ten-Digit Long Code, or more commonly shortened as 10DLC, is intended specifically for sending Application-to-Person (A2P). 


What are FIFO topics on SNS ?
ans : Amazon SNS FIFO (first in, first out) topics support delivery to both Amazon SQS standard and FIFO queues to provide 
      customers with flexibility and control when integrating distributed applications that require data consistency in near real-time.


What is SNS Mobile Push ?
ans : the ability to send push notification messages directly to apps on mobile devices.

On which delivery method do we use and configure the subscription ?
ans : You use and set up subscriptions through the delivery method specified by the service or product, typically online platforms 
      where you subscribe and manage your recurring payments or content access.
